The paper focuses on a novel system concept to solve the massive access problem in future communication systems, which falls under the domain of information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The use of a Hardware-In-the-Loop (HIL) measurement setup suggests a focus on system design and implementation, which could fall under systems and control (cs.SY). The scenarios tested include a machine hall, which suggests a focus on multimedia (cs.MM), and the achieved reliability suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) for improving system performance.
